OL,6,FTB is the world's leading cause of
OL,7,Fdeath from a single infectious agent,
OL,8,Fhaving surpassed coronavirus. It is a
OL,9,Fbacterial infection that most
OL,10,Ffrequently affects the lungs, which is
OL,11,Fwhen it is infectious. The World
OL,12,FHealth Organisation estimates that
OL,13,F10.8 million people were ill with TB
OL,14,Fin 2023, a 7% increase from 2020.
OL,16,FHowever, the bacterium that causes TB
OL,17,Fcan also lie dormant for many years,
OL,18,Fsomething known as latent TB.
